TITLE: Levi Strauss hikes dividend as second-quarter earnings exceed expectations
SUMMARY: Levi Strauss second quarter earnings topped analyst estimates.

TITLE: Samsung's 'better than feared' earnings spur chip stock rally
SUMMARY: Samsung's second quarter earnings guidance, which provided relief for investors, helped drag up shares of chipmakers TSMC, UMC and SK Hynix.

TITLE: Walgreens profits squeezed as Covid vaccine wanes, health-care investment rises
SUMMARY: The drugstore reiterated its forecast for the year after seeing online purchases jump and retail sales bounce back in the quarter.

TITLE: RH shares slide after company lowers its outlook for the year
SUMMARY: High-end furniture chain RH on Wednesday slashed its outlook for 2022 revenue.

TITLE: Bed Bath & Beyond replaces CEO as retailer's sales plummet
SUMMARY: The home goods retailer has faced months of challenges, with supply chain woes and pressure from activist investor Ryan Cohen.

TITLE: Nike earnings top Wall Street's expectations, despite inflation in the U.S. and Covid lockdowns in China
SUMMARY: Nike posted better-than-expected sales and profit for its fiscal fourth quarter.

TITLE: Olive Garden's parent company Darden beats earnings estimates as sales jump
SUMMARY: Olive Garden's parent company issued a mixed forecast for fiscal 2023 as it prepares to face inflation and economic uncertainty.

TITLE: Adobe shares move lower after full-year projections fall short
SUMMARY: Adobe cited foreign-exchange challenges, along with other software companies, as well as the war in Ukraine when it gave lower-than-expected guidance.

TITLE: Oracle shares rise on better-than-expected earnings report
SUMMARY: Oracle exceeded estimates on the top and bottom lines for its fiscal fourth quarter.

TITLE: DocuSign shares crater after first-quarter earnings miss
SUMMARY: DocuSign has struggled this year alongside the rest of the cloud software sector.

TITLE: Credit Suisse issues profit warning for second quarter, citing Ukraine war and rate hikes
SUMMARY: Credit Suisse said on Wednesday that it is likely to post a loss for the second quarter as the war in Ukraine and monetary policy tightening squeeze its investment bank.

TITLE: Target expects squeezed profits from aggressive plan to get rid of unwanted inventory
SUMMARY: Target said it will take a short-term hit from markdowns, but wants to clear room for groceries, back-to-school supplies and other items consumers want.

TITLE: Lululemon raises guidance as customers keep spending despite higher prices
SUMMARY: Lululemon expects the momentum in its business to continue in spite of broader economic headwinds.

TITLE: Microsoft lowers fourth-quarter guidance, citing unfavorable foreign exchange rates
SUMMARY: In an investor slide deck, Microsoft said it lowered its revenue guidance as a result of unfavorable foreign exchange rate movement.

TITLE: GameStop reports $158 million loss and decline in hardware sales
SUMMARY: GameStop reported its first-quarter 2022 earnings after the bell on Wednesday.

TITLE: Salesforce stock jumps as it raises profit forecast, CFO says company will be more 'measured' in hiring
SUMMARY: Salesforce now sees a stronger full fiscal year of profitability even as it expects to turn in less revenue than it had previously expected.

TITLE: Victoria's Secret reports better-than-expected profit but warns challenges could persist
SUMMARY: Victoria's Secret reported a quarterly profit that topped Wall Street expectations, but warned that the retail environment will continue to be challenging.

TITLE: Alibaba, Tencent and JD.com all just posted their slowest revenue growth on record
SUMMARY: Chinese tech giants Alibaba, Tencent and JD.com have all posted their slowest revenue growth on record as Covid and Beijing's tech crackdown took their toll.

TITLE: 3 takeaways from Dollar General, Dollar Tree earnings that sent stocks soaring
SUMMARY: Dollar Tree and Dollar General boosted their outlook for the year, noting that shoppers squeezed by inflation will seek cheaper prices.

TITLE: Gap shares tumble nearly 20% after retailer slashes profit guidance for the year
SUMMARY: The lower-income consumer, which is Old Navy's target customer, is starting to feel pinched by inflation, Chief Executive Officer Sonia Syngal told CNBC.

TITLE: Macy's stock surges as company raises 2022 profit outlook despite uncertain retail landscape
SUMMARY: Macy's reaffirmed its fiscal 2022 sales outlook and raised its profit guidance, expecting stronger credit card revenue for the remainder of the year.

TITLE: Nvidia stock falls on light guidance, CFO says company will slow hiring
SUMMARY: The stock dropped in extended trading after the chipmaker gave a light forecast for the current quarter.

TITLE: Snowflake stock falls as executives forecast a narrower margin than expected
SUMMARY: Snowflake maintained its full-year projections, show that it continues to expect revenue growth to slow from its days as a newly minted public company.

TITLE: Dick's shares rally despite lower forecast; company says outdoor hobbies will outlast pandemic
SUMMARY: Dick's trimmed its outlook for the year amid uncertain economic conditions, but the retailer said it isn't yet seeing any dramatic shifts in its business.

TITLE: Nordstrom raises full-year outlook as first-quarter sales top expectations
SUMMARY: CEO Erik Nordstrom said the company has been able to capitalize on demand from people who are shopping for "long-awaited occasions."

TITLE: Abercrombie & Fitch shares fall 29% after retailer posts loss, offers weak outlook
SUMMARY: Abercrombie & Fitch slashed its sales outlook for fiscal 2022, anticipating that economic headwinds will remain at least through the end of the year.

TITLE: Best Buy says softer demand is sticking around, but company isn't planning for a recession
SUMMARY: Best Buy's revenue beat Wall Street's revenue estimates for the fiscal first quarter.

TITLE: Zoom pops 16% on first-quarter earnings beat and strong guidance
SUMMARY: Zoom shares have lost about 85% of their value since peaking October 2020, and are down by more than half this year.

TITLE: Snap plunges 30% after CEO warns company will miss revenue and earnings estimates, slow hiring
SUMMARY: Snap will miss its own targets for revenue and adjusted earnings in the current quarter, CEO Evan Speigel warned on Monday in a note to employees.

TITLE: Palo Alto Networks stock jumps after company lifts full-year forecast
SUMMARY: Palo Alto Networks is benefiting from positive trends in demand for cybersecurity services, CEO Nikesh Arora said in a statement.
